title: Single vehicle crash on I-94 leaves two seriously injured.
text:
Single vehicle crash on I-94 leaves two seriously injured.
Two seriously injured in I-94 rollover; driver charged with DUI refusal and criminal vehicular injury.
DICKINSON â€” A single-vehicle crash on Interstate 94 left two people seriously injured, according to the North Dakota Highway Patrol.
On Feb.19th at 6:37 P.M. a 2002 Chevrolet S10 with two occupants was traveling eastbound on I-94 from Dickinson to Richardton at an alleged speed of 75 MPH. The vehicle left the roadway, entered the median and overturned.
ADVERTISEMENT
The vehicle was carrying two occupants, the driver, a 42 year old male, and the passenger, a 29 year old female. Both passenger and driver were unrestrained at the time of the accident.
The driver of the vehicle has been charged with DUI refusal and criminal vehicular injury.
Both parties suffered serious injuries from the accident. The woman was flown to Fargo to receive further treatment for her injuries.
According to the North Dakota Highway Patrol road conditions at the time of the accident were good and the weather conditions were clear.
The crash remains under investigation by the North Dakota Highway Patrol.
